results.description:
I needed a stock photo of the elf on the shelf for my company’s blog…well, there are basically ZERO options for this…so I made my own, with my own elves!  Using my brand new (had it for 3 hours!) Sigma 18-35 1.8 lens, natural light, an antique bench and a piece of white poster board hanging off the back of my couch, I was able to capture “Randy” and “Gary” the elves perfectly for a blog image.

I hope that you’ll use Randy and Gary as a pic for your blog too!  Enjoy!
